summaries.short: Series premiere. When his mother's new military assignment uproots their family to Italy, 14-year-old Fraser struggles to find his place.
summaries.full: Series premiere. When Sarah Wilson is named the new commander of a difficult military unit in Chioggia, Italy, she uproots her wife Maggie and teenage son Fraser to start a new chapter in this unfamiliar seaside town. Fraser longs for Mark, a friend he left behind in New York, and seems uninterested in connecting with the other teenagers on base--until he meets Caitlin.

summaries.short: Fraser uncovers one of Caitlin's deepest secrets, forever changing their relationship.
summaries.full: The arrival of Caitlin's period accelerates her secret desire to experiment with her gender expression--and to flirt with girls, test boundaries with her boyfriend Sam, and spar with her father Richard. Later, Fraser discovers Caitlin's secret, which forever changes the nature of their relationship.

summaries.short: The dynamics of the friend group shift after Caitlin and Sam's break up. Meanwhile, Sarah and Maggie explore the company of others.
summaries.full: A fracture begins to form within the friend group following Caitlin and Sam's breakup. Maggie attends the Chioggia Festival with the neighborhood women and finds an unexpected companion. Meanwhile, the progress Colonel Wilson has made in her new role is derailed when she decides to deploy her troops early--and her complex relationship with Fraser is rattled.

summaries.short: Before Craig deploys to Afghanistan, his friends throw him an epic wedding.
summaries.full: With his deployment timeline fast-tracked, Craig spontaneously proposes to his Italian girlfriend, Valentina. Determined to ship him off with a celebration he'll never forget, his friends pool their resources for a Hawaiian-themed wedding that leads to an evening of debauchery.
